{{Infobox number | number = 119 | divisor = 1, 7, 17, 119 }} '''119''' ('''one hundred [and] nineteen''') is the [[natural number]] following [[118 (number)|118]] and preceding [[120 (number)|120]].
== Mathematics == * 119 is a [[Perrin number]], preceded in the sequence by 51, 68, 90 (it is the sum of the first two mentioned).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oeis.org/A001608|title=Sloane's A001608 : Perrin sequence|last=|first=|date=|website=The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences|publisher=OEIS Foundation|access-date=2016-05-27}}</ref> * 119 is the sum of five consecutive [[Prime number|primes]] (17 + 19 + 23 + 29 + 31). * 119 is a [[highly cototient number]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oeis.org/A100827|title=Sloane's A100827 : Highly cototient numbers|last=|first=|date=|website=The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences|publisher=OEIS Foundation|access-date=2016-05-27}}</ref> * 119 is the [[Order (group theory)|order]] of the largest [[Cyclic group|cyclic]] [[subgroups]] of the [[Monster group]].<ref>J. H. Conway et al.: Atlas of Finite Groups. Clarendon Press, Oxford, 1985. {{ISBN|0-19-853199-0}} (Page 223)</ref> * 119 is the smallest [[composite number]] that is 1 less than a [[factorial]] (120 is 5!). * 119 is a biprime, and the third in the {7.q} family.
==Telephony== * [[1-1-9]] is an emergency telephone number in some countries * A number to report children / youth at risk in France<ref>[http://www.allo119.gouv.fr/ Descriptive website]</ref> * 119 is the emergency number in Afghanistan that belongs to police and interior ministry. * The [[South Korea|South Korean]] emergency call number. * The [[China]] fire station call number.
==Other== * 119 is the default [[Computer port (software)|port]] for unencrypted NNTP connections. * [[Project 119]] is a governmental program of the People's Republic of China targeting sports that China has not traditionally excelled in at the [[Summer Olympics]], to maximize the amount of medals won during the games. * 119 is also the atomic number of the theoretical element [[ununennium]].
