'''Georges Gonthier''' is one of the leading practitioners in [[Formal proof|formal mathematics]]. He led the formalization of the [[four color theorem]] and [[Feit–Thompson theorem|Feit–Thompson proof of the odd-order theorem]]. (Both were written using the [[proof assistant]] [[Coq]].)
== See also == * [[Kepler conjecture#A formal proof|Flyspeck proof]] led by [[Thomas Callister Hales]]
